//
Psychology is the scientific study of human behaviour and mental processes.

Scientific Science -> Psychological science relies on emperical evidence as a way of knowing about how we think, feel and behave.  
Behaviour -> Any action caused by any stimulus. Too sensitive, affected by so many specific variables and their interactions.
            Behaviour is a function of attributes of the person and environment.

What is the goal?
-> Ultimate goal is to modify human behaviour in order to enhance efficiency and well being that will affect leading to the overall
productivity of the individual. Or to make a person more happy, adaptive nd efficient.

// Research 
-> basic research -> Attempt to develop principles of behaviour and mental processes.
-> Applies research -> Application of psychological principles in solving individual or organizational's issues in order to make them more 
efficient.
